        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 22 at 3:43PM MDT by NWS Albuquerque NM</headline>
        <description>At 343 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a line of strong
thunderstorms extending from 12 miles northwest of Newkirk to over
Puerto De Luna, moving east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Santa Rosa, Cuervo, Newkirk, Santa Rosa Lake State Park and Puerto
De Luna.

This includes the following highways...
Interstate 40 between Mile Markers 270 and 302.
State Road 104 between Mile Markers 59 and 69.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
